         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Queenscliff 16/9/67 ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ I have the honor to solicit that you will be pleased to sanction the expenditure additionally of fifty pounds Sterling for earthworks, garden arrangement &amp; more extended...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">67.09.16</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To James Grant</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">P67/10542, unit 631, VPRS 44/P inward registered and unregistered correspondence, VA 538 Department of Crown Lands and Survey, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Queenscliff 16/9/67</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor to solicit that you will be pleased to sanction the expenditure additionally of fifty pounds Sterling for earthworks, garden arrangement &amp; more extended gravelling at Toorack. The original estimate was three hundred pounds<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The estimate made in M to J. Grant 9 August 1867 (in this edition as 67-08-09a)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>£297:1: 4<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was regarded as an overestimate, see notes to that letter. Notes to M to M to D. Gillies, 29 June 1868 rehearse the background to this letter<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>but only one hundred has been expended yet. I venture to draw your attention to the fact, that the Duke of Edinburgh may possibly arrive already in the beginning of next month &amp; that thus the early completion of this work at Toorack appears to me very recommendable</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your very obedient</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The honorable Jam. Macph. Grant &amp;c &amp;c &amp;c<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M was informed by W. Wardell, Inspector General of Public Works, on 26 September 1867 that M. Hervey, Commissioner of Public Works, was 'unable to spare anything out of the sum granted for new works under this Department as it [was] not only exhausted but already overdrawn'.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See also E.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Agg to M, 31 March 1869<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 69-03-31a).</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; color: #C00000; "
                        xml:lang="en">But how do we know it is this issue with which Ogg is concerned.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
